.TH "tipc_shutdown" 9 "tipc_shutdown" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tipc_shutdown \- shutdown socket connection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tipc_shutdown
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "int how "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket structure
.IP "how" 12
direction to close (must be SHUT_RDWR)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Terminates connection (if necessary), then purges socket's receive queue.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, errno otherwise
